name: POP 4 FREAKS
description:
You’re a total creepy freak, but make it POP!

Popular ballads that when you really look close at the lyrics are kinda not IT, ya know. Lyrics matter for this one.

name: The Metamorphosis
description:
Submit a song that showcases dynamic transformations from beginning to end. Whether it's a change in tempo, instrumentation, or mood, I want to hear tracks that take listeners on a journey and evolve into something unexpected. From subtle shifts to dramatic transformations, show us how songs can evolve and surprise us.
No Stairway to Heaven, no Space Oddity, no Bohemian Rhapsody, no Baba O’Riley.

name: ~*aesthetic shivers*~
description: AKA frisson, psychogenic shivers, musically induced chills, etc. submit a song that gives you goosebumps, for whatever reason. If frisson isn’t something you experience, submit a song that really stirs you and gets you feeling some way fr fr.

name: Narrative Bops
description: Songs that tell a story (like an actual story - not "this chord progression takes the listener on an emotional journey" story)

name: Get Under the Covers
description: It's a covers playlist baby! You know what to do.

name: Melodic Tracks
description: The beat of the song must not be audible, meaning no songs with drums, beatboxing, or traditional percussion instruments. Instruments like the piano, which are technically percussion, are allowed. The requirement is that the rhythm section (not rhythm itself) must be absent from the song.

name: Atypical Instrumentation
description:
Looking for songs that feature uncommon or strange instruments, non-standard usage of instruments, or idiosyncratic ways of playing instruments. What counts as strange/uncommon is up to you, but like, a band with synthesizers don't count. Your pick has to have been released between 2014 and now. 

Pop music with weird tropical cuica samples absolutely counts.

name: Locals Only!
description:
Time to shout out your buddies band! Do you have a cousin who's a DJ, does your boyfriends bff play in a klezmer band, are you in love with a weird punk band that plays in a swamp down under? This playlist is for them!
The rules:
1) You must know someone in the band 
2) if you don't know anyone in the band, they have to be based in the city/nearest largest city you live in (or have lived in very recently)
3) play count of the song has to be 50K or less (or if it's more- not in the top 5 songs)

name: Juke Jams
description:
#nudes
It's time for some juke jams. The songs that make you feel sexy. When you get that feeling, put this playlist on, and get you some healing.

name: OST ROUND
description:
Songs that were written for a movie or made popular by a movie.

Include the name of the movie in the public comment!

name: Dumb and dumber
description: Songs that slap, but when you listen to them you know that they've somehow made you dumber.

name: Hello from the other side
description:
Hello from the other side:

Music for Victorian ghost children. 

Spooky sounds, ghostly narratives and haunting imagery. Your song doesn’t need to be from the Victorian era, but it does to have dusty charm. 

No horror movie OSTs!

name: Script Kiddies
description:
Script Kiddies
Pick a song which is sung in a language with a non-Latin script. English, French, Spanish, et al. are out, but everything from Chinese to Javanese scripts are fair game. The more disoriented you feel by the script, and therefore the language, the better.

Use https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_languages_by_writing_system as a source of inspiration.

name: TV Theme
description: You’re life is turned into a 30 minute sitcom. What’s your theme song?

name: FUNKY ROLLER RINK PARTY
description:
Songs for July cool dancing on skates
Songs need at least a lil bounce to them
Picture Skokie dinner society as a roller-skate crew with entrance choreography, short shorts, knee socks and a few impressive roller skate tricks to whip out if you need inspo
Disco music is not forbidden or discouraged and will likely be embraced but remember roller rinks and funkiness existed in the 80s/90s/00s/10s too! 
No slow songs for couples skate allowed!
